      "type": "thought",
      "text": "I found it! The \"Binary Intent Gateway BIG.pdf\" is indeed an API documentation for the Binary Intent Gateway system. This is the closest thing to what the user was looking for - it describes the OpenMRS REST API mapping (Table 1 shows opcodes mapped to OpenMRS REST API endpoints like `GET /ws/rest/v1/patient/{uuid}`, `POST /ws/rest/v1/obs`, etc.).\n\nHowever, this is about \"gateway\" not \"getaway\". Let me check if the user might have meant \"gateway\" or if there's another file. Let me also check the \"The Binary Intent Gateway Establishing a Deterministic.pdf\" file.Actually, the user specifically said \"getaway api doc\" not \"gateway api doc\". \n\nBut maybe they meant \"gateway\" - these Binary Intent Gateway files are the only API documentation I've found. I should present this to the user and ask for clarification, or check if there's a \"New Full Document.pdf\" on the desktop that might be what they're looking for.",
